"a.凸出的 【英】 adj. 凸出的 (curving outward) 【记】 参考：concave(凹入) ，比较：vex(使…苦 恼) n. /adj. 凸出的(如球体的外表面) 【参】concave(v /n 凹); vex(vt 使烦恼; 恼怒) 【反】dent(n 凹; 凹痕) 【记】vex是达到vertex顶点时的路径，从凸面走到顶点；curv + ex 向外弯的curv 【相关】apex顶点，axis轴，climax顶点 convex (adj.)  1570s, from Middle French convexe, from Latin convexus ""vaulted, arched,"" past participle of convehere ""to bring together,"" from com- ""together,"" or ""thoroughly"" (see com-) + vehere ""to bring"" (see vehicle). Possibly from the idea of vaults carried together to meet at the point of a roof. Related: Convexity. Convex lens is from 1822."
